comment: We can always find values matching ` x ` and ` y ` , as long as they are represented by distinct variables. This theorem merges two ~ ax6e instances ` E. z z = x ` and ` E. w w = y ` into a common expression. Alan Sare contributed a variant of this theorem with distinct variable conditions before, see ~ ax6e2nd . (Contributed by Wolf Lammen, 27-Sep-2018.)
